node.title: Covid-19: No sign of virus after testing in Taranaki
node.description: There have been no positive cases of Covid-19 picked up in testing in Taranaki over the weekend, after the virus was detected in wastewater.
node.content:
["There have been no positive cases of Covid-19 picked up in testing in Taranaki over the weekend, after the was detected in wastewater.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Simon Rogers\n
", "The sample came from the town of Stratford and around a thousand tests have been completed in the region since Friday.", "Taranaki DHB's incident management controller Becky Jenkins said around 600 tests have returned a negative reading.", "She said the highest testing rates were in Stratford East and West, with M\u0101ori testing rates per head of population higher in those areas.", "The results of recent wastewater samples in Taranaki are expected to be available on Wednesday."]
